      "side": 1,
      "message": "In practice it seems like most uses are coming from a uint8_t* or other low-level type that is being used as a raw pointer into a blob of flexibly-typed memory. Looking at most callers, I get the impression that it\u0027s basically used to type-pun/cast `src` to type Dest, and the raw type of `src` was irrelevant because we\u0027re explicitly saying it\u0027s actually type Dest. I guess it would still be weird if `src` was actually some high-level type though, so if you want me to add a check, I can.",
