      "writtenOn": "2020-07-23T22:45:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done.\n\nI changed it because it seemed like it made generic code harder to write, but it probably doesn\u0027t come up much in practice. (e.g. why shouldn\u0027t I be able to widen_cast a bool to uint32? Size will be equal on some platforms and greater on others.)\n\nBTW, one thing I was wondering--we don\u0027t value-initialize dst here:\n\n   Dest dst{};\n\nDo we actually generate better code by using default-initialization? It seems like it limits the utility of widen_cast if you might have noise in the top bits. e.g. I can\u0027t use this to make a GLSLProcessorKey.",
      "parentUuid": "6fb8ecf4_10bb37a2",
